pageContext.claim: “I was at the opening of the $10 billion Cameron LNG export facility in Hackberry, Louisiana, employing thousands and thousands of Louisiana workers. They couldn't get their permits for years. I got them real fast. … For years and years they tried to get those permits, they couldn't get them. I got them very fast and we cut a ribbon a couple of months ago.”
pageContext.analysis: Sempra Energy announced its plan to create an LNG export terminal in 2012 in a partnership with Japanese companies. The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission authorized the project, located in Hackberry, La., in June 2014 under Barack Obama.
